        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stop Sexual Harassment in K-12 Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill outlines the role and duties of Title IX coordinators in elementary and secondary schools, including by requiring local educational agencies to increase the number of full-time employees designated to serve as a Title IX coordinator per specified student population. The bill also creates a grant program to train teachers and staff on how to respond to signs of sex-based&amp;nbsp;harassment and assault of students and requires the Department of Education to develop a sex-based harassment&amp;nbsp;survey.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
